<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19493] Optionally fail writes when SAI refuses to index a term value exceeding a configured maximum size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19493</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SAI currently emits a client warning when we try to index a text value larger than &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.sai.max_string_term_size&lt;/tt&gt;. It might be nice to have a hard limit as well, above which we can reject the mutation entirely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
